WorkItem.Description:
I'm trying to load the attached document (a list of delicious bookmarks) but receive the following stackoverflow error: "An unhandled exception of type 'System.StackOverflowException' occurred in mscorlib.dll".  This can be easily produced using the attached document,  the code works fine on smaller documents but blows up on this document which is much larger and contains over 6000 bookmarks.  Any help or guidance would be greatly appreciated.  The error details and steps to reproduce are below.
 
It is very easy to reproduce, the statement I use to load the file is:
 
HtmlDocument htmlDoc = new HtmlAgilityPack.HtmlDocument();
htmlDoc.OptionFixNestedTags = true;
htmlDoc.Load(@"C:\delicious-20110220.htm", System.Text.Encoding.UTF8);
 
The portion of code the application crashes on in the debugger is:
 
        IEnumerator<HtmlNode> IEnumerable<HtmlNode>.GetEnumerator()
        {
            return _items.GetEnumerator();
        }
